
If you are interested in a more detailed technical description or user guide please visit the following URL:
http://www.knowarc.eu/download/D3.2-1_08_documentation.pdf
IMPORTANT:
    The command line tools are the parts of ARC1 software and using they services. This is because you
    can't use them alone, and will have to install along with the complete ARC1.

Client library and command line interfaces to the gLite servers through the CREAM interface
gliteclean - clean job using CREAM interface
glitedelegate - create CREAM delegation
glitekill - kill job using CREAM interface
glitestat - get the job status using CREAM interface
glitesub - submit a new job using CREAM interface
gliteundelegeate - destroy CREAM delegation
